      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just to be on the safe side: Jami also supports offline communication, right? Does this patch take this feature into account—meaning, it prevents a peer from appearing as unavailable even though offline communication would be possible? Or do they show up as online even without internet access if offline communication via local Wi-Fi/WLAN is available? That is, assuming this patch is related to that at all.",
